text: Dolná Krupá is a village in the Trnava Region of Slovakia. It is in the Danubian Hills at around 12 km from the city of Trnava. The important sights in the village are: * the Saint Andrew church, built in 1807–1811 * the Dolná Krupá mansion. == Population == == References == Category:Villages in Slovakia Category:Trnava Region
title: Dolná Krupá
